<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-02-28T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-02-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="782" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d782">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">816.51/107: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Salvador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Schuyler</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-02-28T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February 28,
                                        1922—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>7. Department’s January 31, 6 p.m.</p>
                        <p>Department informed that loan contract and purchase contract signed
                            February 11th. You will therefore acknowledge note received from Foreign
                            Minister as previously instructed. Department desires that Government of
                            Salvador should reply taking note of <pb facs="1000" n="886" xml:id="pg_886"/> fact that this Government reserves liberty of
                            action with regard to future diplomatic representations as stated in
                            your acknowledgment.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>